metadata.name: MASKED MENACE
metadata.description:
"Masked Menace" is a title that emphasizes the dark and ominous quality of the artwork. The word "menace" suggests that there is something threatening or dangerous about the character, which is reinforced by the description of the skull mask and the overall tone of the painting.

The word "masked" adds another layer of meaning to the title, as it suggests that the character is hiding his true identity or intentions behind the mask. Masks are often used in art and literature to represent deception, mystery, or the duality of human nature. In this case, the mask may be seen as a symbol of the character's hidden motives or intentions, which are hinted at but not fully revealed in the artwork.

Overall, "Masked Menace" is a title that captures the dark, mysterious, and threatening qualities of the artwork, while also suggesting deeper layers of meaning and symbolism."
